  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\r\n\r\n2.12.6\r\n\r\n### What happened?\r\n\r\nWhen using the hardhat fork functionality, when a preexisting contract tries to write to a preciously not set slot it trows an error with the message \r\n\r\nI'm calling the USDC.approve function with a owner, spender pair previously not set.\r\nimpersonated account: 0x1A7bc54e0F613f01103Be443ee98995Ce2754C75\r\nparams: 0x1A7bc54e0F613f01103Be443ee98995Ce2754C75, 10,\r\nerror: Transaction reverted and Hardhat couldn't infer the reason\r\n\r\n### Minimal reproduction steps\r\n\r\n\r\nI made two tests after with the custom contract Test\r\n\r\n### Test.sol file\r\n```solidity\r\n// SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\r\npragma solidity ^0.8.0;\r\n\r\ncontract Test {    \r\n    function approve(address, uint) \r\n    external {\r\n        assembly {\r\n            sstore(0x1000, 0x1000)\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Test 1\r\nIn the first test I deploy a Test contract and rewrote the implementation slot in USDC with hardhat_setStorageAt,\r\nwhen the same USDC.approve is called it gives the same error as before\r\n\r\n### Test 2\r\nin the second test is similar but before calling the approve function I rewrote the slot 0x1000 (the one used in the Test contract) wih hardhat_setStorageAt. now the function executes with no error\r\n\r\n### Search terms\r\n\r\nfork, error, 'Error: Transaction reverted and Hardhat couldn't infer the reason.'",
